WEBVTT

00:00:02.780 --> 00:00:05.851
There's always the custom that when a person is about to die,

00:00:05.851 --> 00:00:08.360
they first make a wish and then they bury them.

00:00:09.940 --> 00:00:12.585
There was a person who used a wheelchair

00:00:12.585 --> 00:00:14.503
and when he was about to die,

00:00:14.503 --> 00:00:18.140
with all his family around his bed, he made his wish.

00:00:18.140 --> 00:00:21.320
When I die, I want them to put it inside the coffin.

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:25.720
And the family granted his wish.

00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:27.714
The day of the funeral arrived,

00:00:27.714 --> 00:00:30.466
and the family buried him with his wheelchair.

00:00:31.420 --> 00:00:32.852
The second person was blind,

00:00:32.852 --> 00:00:35.360
and when he was about to die, with all his family

00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:37.100
around his bed, he made his wish.

00:00:37.100 --> 00:00:38.933
I want that when I die, please,

00:00:38.933 --> 00:00:40.420
and the family granted it.

00:00:40.420 --> 00:00:43.967
When he died, at the funeral they buried the blind person

00:00:43.967 --> 00:00:46.326
and placed his cane inside the coffin.

00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:49.805
And the third was an oral deaf person,

00:00:49.805 --> 00:00:52.635
and when he was about to die with all his family

00:00:52.635 --> 00:00:53.700
he made his wish.

00:00:53.700 --> 00:00:54.103
I wish,

00:00:54.103 --> 00:00:55.600
and his family granted it.

00:00:55.600 --> 00:00:58.090
When they buried him, they put the cochlear implant

00:00:58.090 --> 00:00:59.983
and the hearing aid inside the coffin.

00:01:01.340 --> 00:01:03.064
Then came a signing deaf person,

00:01:03.064 --> 00:01:05.596
and when he was about to die, he made his wish,

00:01:05.596 --> 00:01:06.620
and they granted it.

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:10.122
When the burial was held, they brought the live interpreter

00:01:10.122 --> 00:01:13.120
in handcuffs and buried her with the deaf person.
